The defendant Oliver M Denavas was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • 4th Degree Sexual Assault, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.225(3m).
  • Disorderly Conduct, a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Defendant Oliver M Denavas in court with attorney Edward J. Hunt.  Joshua M. Mathy appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Sentencing proceeded.
Statements to the court by counsels and the defendant.  Additional statements by Peter W., Dana A., Sarah H., Jerry J.
AS TO BOTH COUNTS THE COURT WILL AUTHORIZE THE TRANSFER OF SENTENCE TO WALWORTH COUNTY.
AS to count 1:
Court sentenced the defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Correction; credit for 0 days served.  Court STAYED sentence and placed defendant on PROBATION for 1 YEAR with the following conditions:
-Follow all rules of probation.
-No further violations of the law.
-Sex offender assessment and treatment.
-No contact with the victim.
-Maintain employment.
-Other counseling needs to be determined.
-Perform 50 HOURS of community service at a non-profit agency.
-Provide DNA sample and pay all costs.
-Pay victim witness surcharge and all costs, assessments and surcharges, DNA surcharge.
-Pay restitution of $908.53 to Crime Victim Compensation Fund which is stipulated to by defendant.
AS to count 2:
The Court ordered the Defendant to serve 90 days in the House of Correction, the FIRST 30 DAYS to be served with huber privileges for work/counseling/community service.  The balance of 60 days to be STAYED for review on 1-20-2015 at 8:15am.
The court will allow defendant until 4pm on 11-14-2014 to report in Walworth County.
If needed, counsel may obtain an order to allow the defendant to travel outside Wisconsin.
Court orders payment of all courts, assessments and surcharges, DNA surcharge.

AS TO EACH OF THE COUNTS:  Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of NO CONTEST.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the AMENDED Information and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
Case is adjourned to 10-24-2014 at 8:15 for sentencing.
